  "1.20.1": {
    "1.2.3": "- Updated to new Aether 1.0.0 beta 2\n- Updated Aerwhale King boss bar\n- Fixed incorrect use of accessory tags. Should work with the normal curios slots now.\n- Baby winged animals inherit their wing color from their parents\n- Phoenix tools are properly considered as Aether tools",
    "1.2.2": "- Updated to work with Aether 1.0.0-beta.1.4",
    "1.2.1": "- Fixed programmer art Moa textures\n- Music discs and armor trim are tagged as dungeon items",
    "1.2.0": "- Updated to 1.20.1\n- Added Noble Armor Trim, obtained as a treasure item from the Platinum Dungeon for beating the boss. Can be duplicated using Gale Stone\n- Fixed some quirks with the Aerwhale King\u0027s attack pattern"
  },
  "1.19.4": {
    "1.1.7": "- Fixed incompatibility with latest Aether beta",
    "1.1.6": "- Fixed a quirk with the Aerwhale King\u0027s AI",
    "1.1.5": "- Updated to work with Aether beta 6.1\n- Added new boss theme to the Aerwhale King, Sovereign of the Skies by Jesterguy. The song changes dynamically based on the boss phase. Can be fully disabled via config.\n- Added Royal Music Disc, which plays the Aerwhale King\u0027s boss theme. This is always available regardless of if the boss music itself is disabled.",
    "1.1.4": "- Updated to work with new Aether beta\n- Fixed missing recipes for Gale related blocks",
    "1.1.3": "- Phoenix Tools no longer set fire to enemies, instead they do 20% increased damage to enemies that are on fire. This brings a need for Fire Aspect.\n- Increased damage output of Phoenix Tools\n- Blocks mined with Phoenix Tools drop experience when they normally would.\n- Phoenix Cape should fire earlier, and will also work in The End.\n- Decreased Zanite count in the Platinum Dungeon chests\n- Platinum Dungeons are spaced out more\n- The Aerwhale King will turn invisible during the fog phase. This affects nothing normally, but does affect users with disabled fog, and keeps the fight semi-normal regardless.\n- Invincibility Gem has durability\n- Sentry Shield has less durability\n- Power Gloves have significantly increased durability\n- Shield of Emile will properly block damage once more",
    "1.1.2": "- Increased height of the Aerwhale King\u0027s boss tracking\n- Slowed down Orange Moa speed increase, it now takes longer to get to max speed\n- Pink Aerclouds are mined properly with a hoe",
    "1.1.1": "- Fixed a possible crash with the Aerwhale King in multiplayer\n- Fixed Orange Moa eggs being unable to be incubated\n- Adjusted balance of the Phoenix Axe\n- Adjusted how the Sentry Shield behaves with fire, and other rapidly damaging sources",
    "1.1.0": "- Updated to 1.19.4\n- Revamped the Aerwhale King\n- Retextured everything, classic textures available as a built-in resourcepack.\n- Swetty Mask can now be used to prevent Elytra crash damage.\n- Added Orange Moa, removed after Aether Legacy. Builds up speed as it goes straight.\n- Added Legacy music disc, removed after Aether Legacy.\n- Added option to give Valkyries halos, removed after Aether Legacy.\n- Added options to enable sounds and wing colors, based on the scrapped Aether II: Mutation update\n- Removed Zephyroo, as it will be added to the official Genesis of the Void addon.\n- Renamed Shield of Jeb to Shield of Emile, due to the Hammer of Notch being renamed to Hammer of Kingbdogz\n- Shield of Emile can be used to reflect projectiles\n- Gravitite Shield knocks back enemies\n- Brown Moa eggs are now laid by Blue and Orange moas when nearby one-another. This is in reference to them originally going to be a crossbreed."
  },
  "1.12.2": {
    "1.0.2": "- Updated to support Aether Legacy v1.5.0\n- Menu toggle now overrides the existing Aether menu, it has proper button placements when outside the native resolution, unlike the normal Aether one. It also displays a nice Aether Dirt background.\n- Songstones play a sound when activated"
  }
}
